  "doc_id": "61019",
  "text": "The training data for modeling must be representative of the characteristics of the image sets in the study. Special attention should be paid to collecting and constructing an appropriate dataset for any segmentation system for CNN. Patients undergoing radiotherapy for rectal cancer are generally treated either in a prone position to reduce the volume of small bowel in the high-dose region [CITATION_1] or in a supine position as it is much more stable. [CITATION_2] A different positioning orientation (prone or supine) will result in variability [CITATION_3] in location, shape, and volume of the structures of interest. These differences may affect segmentation performance when training and testing across different positioning orientations.",
